# RW-PROD-003 A1+A2 — engine self-render SHA-256 baseline.
#
# This file is the CANONICAL sha256sum-format fingerprint for the
# minimal even-dimension (2×2, 0.1s, 1fps, ColorHex=#000000) render that pkg/bootstrap's
# runEngineSelfRender step drives through the C++ engine on boot.
#
# The bootstrap reads this file, computes SHA-256 over the output of:
#   pkg/video/pipeline.Runner -> RenderClient().Render(synthetic plan)
# and rejects the worker (code: engine_selftest_baseline_mismatch) if
# the strings differ.
#
# Why sha256sum format (<hex> + 2 spaces +  filename):
#   `sha256sum -c` is the canonical regeneration tool; the parser in
#   pkg/bootstrap.readBaselineSHA256 supports both this format AND a
#   plain single-hex line, so ad-hoc regeneration scripts can choose.
#
# Regeneration:
#   1. Build the worker-agent binary against a pinned C++ engine
#      build. The build number lives in $WORK_DIR/VERSION.txt.
#   2. Run `make bootstrap-smoke` (this Makefile target builds the
#      agent binary with a one-shot CLI argv that creates the
#      render-frame.mp4 alongside this file).
#   3. `sha256sum render-frame.mp4 > tests/fixtures/engine_selftest_baseline.sha256`
#   4. Commit. NEVER regenerate without bumping VERSION.txt — the
#      invariant is bundle-version ≡ engine-binary ≡ baseline-SHA.
#
985f1c38959897ca69a07408211277769b4c48a43c2dc85daad0a53c76f2f49e  tests/fixtures/engine_selftest_baseline.sha256
